FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1781808494
OL,3,CBank of England holds interest rates
OL,4,Cbut warns more inflation yet to come
OL,6,FSince April's meeting of the Bank's
OL,7,Frate setters inflation has fallen back
OL,8,Fto 2.8% but the Bank warns that they
OL,9,Fexpect inflation to rise as the year
OL,10,Fgoes on because the full impact of
OL,11,Fhigh energy prices are yet to be felt.
OL,13,FThe Food and Drink Federation still
OL,14,Fwarns of food price inflation hitting
OL,15,Fdouble digits by the end of the year
OL,16,Fas high energy costs filter through
OL,17,Finto production.
OL,19,FIt is in that context that the Bank
OL,20,Fhas opted for the caution of its
OL,21,Ffourth hold in a row.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1781808494
OL,3,CBank of England holds interest rates
OL,4,Cbut warns more inflation yet to come
OL,6,FAndrew Bailey, Governor of the Bank of
OL,7,FEngland said: "We've held Bank Rate at
OL,8,F3.75% today.
OL,10,F"Oil prices have fallen in recent days
OL,11,Fand that's encouraging... Whatever
OL,12,Fhappens in the future the higher
OL,13,Fenergy prices of the past four months
OL,14,Fmean there's already some inflationary
OL,15,Fpressure in the pipeline.
OL,17,F"The Bank's job is to make sure that
OL,18,Fdoesn't turn into sustained inflation
OL,19,Fabove our 2% target."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
